{
  "stem": "1062.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, a ticket to New York, as a joke.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I had to start all over again, go back to Satu Mare, start going through borders and coming back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I met up-- in Vienna I met up with a Berihah.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Berihah was a-- was a-- like the, the underground from Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Their, their, their job was to-- their job was to smuggle out all the Jews from Europe into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was before there was a Jewish state.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from there, I was taken to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in Bergen-Belsen, I joined-- I stayed in Bergen-Belsen in a DP camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there I joined a Zionist foundation called Noam.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Noam.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Noam is called in Hebrew [HEBREW], The United Youth, United Youth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But Noam is also-- you know, after Tisha B'Av, after we read the Torah from Tisha B'Av, there is the [NON-ENGLISH], I mean, the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It's the first of Torah after Tisha B'Av, after the destruction of the Temple.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were called Noam and [NON-ENGLISH] is about the same thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we joined there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember Ben-Gurion coming there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in 1946.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a conference in Basel and Ben-Gurion came.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With a Zionist organization from Basel he came to Bergen-Belsen, because Basel was the first city where the first Zionist Congress was held and the last Zionist Congress was held.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Ben-Gurion came through.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember he made the remark that we are like ashes left over from the, from the, from the conflagration, you know, from Europe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we didn't like that, so some of our people went up and told Ben-Gurion, listen, what you see is ashes, but behind those ashes are coal, burning coals.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Don't ever call us ashes again.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
